The programme aims to provide support to pupils who have not been able to meet the requirements of 2016 . JOHANNESBURG - The Basic Education Department has called on all pupils who failed matric exams to try again through a specially designed Second Chance Programme.It aims to provide support to pupils who have not been able to meet the requirements of 2016 national senior certificate exams.Pupils who want to advantage of the opportunity are advised to contact their nearest district offices.The department's Troy Martens says: If they only failed two subjects for example that they need to pass the year, they can register for the supplementary examinations which will be written in March and then if they failed the entire year, they can register for the entire Second Chance Programme. (Edited by Neo Koza)